). Unique to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grimaldi" authorityYear="2018" box="[494,535,1682,1707]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Litoleptis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tico">
<emphasis box="[494,535,1682,1707]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">tico</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are branches of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[751,760,1695,1712]" fontSize="7" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">1</subScript>
-M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[797,806,1695,1712]" fontSize="7" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">2</subScript>
fork curved (vs. virtually straight); crossvein cua-m very short (ca. 0.5× length of r-m crossvein, vs. slightly longer than r-m in 
<emphasis box="[108,337,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
